-- Japan transport minister: to unveil JAL support today
-- 
-- Mon Jan 18, 2010 9:33pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/01/19/us-jal-minister-idUSTRE60I0D320100119

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japan's government will announce measures to support Japan Airlines Corp 9205.T after a state-backed restructuring fund announces its decision on the struggling airline later on Tuesday, Transport Minister Seiji Maehara said at a news conference. 

 JAL, Asia's biggest airline by revenues, is expected to file for one of the country's largest ever bankruptcies later today as part of a restructuring being crafted by the Enterprise Turnaround Initiative Corp of Japan. (Reporting by Nobuhiro Kubo)